# Projects & invoicing

## Primary store: Supabase (UI)

- Web app in `app/` — see `supabase/README.md`.
- Tables: `clients`, `projects`, `time_entries`, `invoices`, `payments`, `organization_settings`.
- Unbilled time: `time_entries.invoice_id IS NULL`.

## Legacy CSV + CLI (bulk / agents)

- `clients/clients.csv` — client master
- `projects/projects.csv` — projects linked to `client_id`, with `default_hourly_rate`
- `projects/time-entries.csv` — hours log; `invoiced=yes` after billing
- `invoices/invoice-registry.csv` — issued invoice index
- `config/invoicing.local.json` or Supabase `organization_settings` — company block, tax flags

## CLI (from repo root)

```bash
python3 scripts/add_project.py client --name "..." --email "..."
python3 scripts/add_project.py project --client CLIENT_ID --name "..." --rate 150
python3 scripts/log_time.py --project PROJECT_ID --hours 2.5 --desc "..."
python3 scripts/generate_invoice.py --project PROJECT_ID --dry-run
python3 scripts/generate_invoice.py --project PROJECT_ID
```

## Rules

- One line per time entry; never delete billed entries.
- `rate_override` on a row overrides project `default_hourly_rate` for that entry only.
- Set `charge_gst` / `charge_qst` in `config/invoicing.json` when registered.
- Generated invoices land in `invoices/issued/`; update registry `status` (draft → sent → paid).
